@weakish: We can, but should we? The [Namecoin Domain Name Specification](https://wiki.namecoin.org/index.php?title=Domain_Name_Specification#Valid_Domains) reads:

> [Valid domain names] must start with a letter, end with a letter or digit, and have as interior characters only letters, digits, and hyphen.
> There are also some restrictions on the length. Labels must be 63 characters or less.
